HEADWORD: Unturn
<hw>Un*turn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>turn</ets>.]</ety> <def>To turn in a reserve way,
especially so as to open something; <as>as, to <ex>unturn</ex> a
key</as>.</def> <rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unturned</ent>⟦br⟧
